Activity: A12 - Discover 5 unique offline security tools

Objective
The goal of this activity was to identify security tools that operate without an internet connection and are used to protect systems, devices, and data

Method
I observed tools available on local devices and in physical environments that provide security without requiring online connectivity. these included software-based tools and hardware security mechanisms.

Findings
The following offline security tools were identified:
1. Antivirus software - detects and removes malware using locally stored virus definitions without needing internet access
2. Disk encryption tools - encrypts data on a device to prevent unauthorised access
3. Password managers - stores and encrypts passwods locally on a device
4. USB drive encryption tools - protects data stored on external drives with encryption
5. Hardware security tokens - provides secure authentication without needing network access 

Security Principle
These tools support confidentiality by protecting sensitive data and integrity by preventing unauthorised changes. they also contribute to availability by ensuring secure access to systems even without internet connectivity

Evidence
- photos in evidence folder

Reflection
This activity helped me understand that effective cybersecurity does not always depend on internet-based tools. offline security tools play a crucial role in protecting data at rest and securing devices in isolated environments.
